            <title>[CASSANDRA-16712] DROP COMPACT STORAGE does not invalidate prepared statements as it should </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16712</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;DROP COMPACT STORAGE&lt;/tt&gt; might change the number of columns of a table but as the prepared statement cache is not invalidate the query will not return the correct set of columns until the statement as been invalidate. That can lead to a surprising behavior where the resultset change at un expected point in time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This problem only affect 3.0 and 3.11&lt;/p&gt;</description>
